<p>The next fortnight is expected to be a net surplus one despite advance tax outflows estimated at 20,000 million rupees.</p>
<p>The first instalment of advance taxes will leave the banking system only towards mid June and most part of the fornight should see easy money conditions.</p>
<p>The surplus liquidity will put a downward pressure on call money rates and we should see a moderate rally in prices of government securities.</p>
<p>Also, the above cash flows do not take into account the amount of 30,000 million rupees lent to RBI through short term repos.</p>
